Companion Animal Surveillance Initiative Software License (CASI-SL)
Version 1.0

This License governs the use, modification, and distribution of the Companion Animal Surveillance Data Collection App (the "Software"), developed for the Companion Animal Surveillance Initiative (CASI) by Dr. Tasha Epp, and her team at the University of Saskatchewan. The Software is designed to collect, store, and analyze veterinary data for the purpose of monitoring and researching diseases in companion animals within western Canadian provinces. Protection of participant data and adherence to ethical standards are paramount. Use of the Software indicates agreement to these terms.

1. Definitions
"The Software" refers to the Companion Animal Surveillance Data Collection App including all its code, documentation, and accompanying materials.
"Participant" refers to any veterinarian or veterinary practice that contributes data to CASI through the Software.
"User" refers to any individual or entity that interacts with the Software, including Participants.
"Confidential Information" refers to any data or information entered into, generated by, or related to the use of the Software.

2. Grant of License
Subject to the terms of this License, the Licensor grants the User a non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to use the Software solely for the purpose of participating in CASI data collection and analysis. This License does not permit commercial use, redistribution, or modification of the Software without prior written consent from the Licensor.

3. Data Privacy and Confidentiality
The User agrees to maintain the highest level of confidentiality with regard to the Confidential Information. The Software includes mechanisms for data encryption and secure data handling; the User must not attempt to circumvent these mechanisms.

4. Ethical Use:
The Software must be used in a manner that is ethical and respects the rights and privacy of all Participants. The User agrees to comply with all applicable laws and ethical guidelines related to research and data collection.

5. Contributions and Modifications
Any modifications to the Software or contributions to its code base must be approved by the Licensor. Such changes must preserve the Software's purpose, ensure data confidentiality, and adhere to ethical standards.

6. Termination
This License is effective until terminated. It will terminate immediately without notice from the Licensor if the User fails to comply with any of its terms and conditions. Upon termination, the User must cease all use of the Software and destroy all copies.

7. Disclaimer of Warranty
The Software is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind, express or implied. The Licensor does not warrant that the Software will meet the User's requirements or that its operation will be uninterrupted or error-free.

8. Limitation of Liability
To the maximum extent permitted by law, in no event will the Licensor be liable for any damages arising out of the use or inability to use the Software.

9. Jurisdiction
This License shall be governed by the laws of Canada and the province of Saskatchewan. Any disputes arising from this License will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Saskatchewan.

10. Acknowledgment of Understanding
By using the Software, the User acknowledges that they have read this License, understand it, and agree to be bound by its terms and conditions.
